Great little app

It's a simple, solid, epic little tool. It runs with a midi keyboard really really well. I think if it had a few more real sampled intstruments, it would be a hit. The interface is refined and easy to use. But my favorite part is the recording feature. It's just so easy and you get to see the notes as they were played. Very cool stuff.
replyContent: Thanks for the praise! We are definitely planning to add more instruments this year. Great to hear you enjoy it and thanks for the feedback.

content: Best piano app I've used. Touch response and "playability" is great, unlike many other apps. Sound is good. I like the options for turning note names on and off, including black keys. Great tool for teaching. Ad free version was very minimal, but it is worth the paying for the full version because a. It's a great app and b. You get a full screen.

If you are looking for an app that displays piano keys and nothing more this is it. Just what I wanted, simplistic and well made app. ((Ads are not annoying at all.)) EDIT: This version is even ad free and very fairly priced. I mainly bought it to support the developers. Fit for ear training excercises on the go (obviously you don't learn how to play piano)
replyContent: Thanks, that exactly the goal of this app! Note that ads are only present in the lite version, not this paid pro one :). Enjoy

THE BEST! Stylishly simple & elegantly useful. No tackiness or silly subscriptions. Piano sizing tool to fit more or less keys is great for different screen sizes. Sliding octave range selector also useful. Works very well with Samsung Galaxy A40 - a mid-range/"budget" phone so expect it to work well with other similar phones & more. I use it for getting the key for notes in choir rehearsals & have recommended it to my fellow choristers. Amazing value for pro version which this review is for.

Since I cannot always be near a piano when I practice singing, this app is a perfect solution. I can practice in my bedroom or even in my parked car. I tried a metronome app but am much happier with this app.
